---
title: Dual-Loop Agent Architecture
---
flowchart TB
    subgraph Outer["Outer Loop (Strategy and Protocol)"]
        direction TB
        Scout["Scout and Plan<BR>(read goals, decompose tasks)"]
        Spec["Define Work Packages<BR>(atomic, testable, non-overlapping)"]
        Packet["Generate Strategy Packet<BR>(goal, commitment diagram, constraints,<BR>acceptance criteria)"]
        Verify["Verify Result<BR>(run tests, check acceptance criteria)"]
        Commit["Seal and Commit<BR>(Outer Loop commits to main branch)"]
        Correct["Generate Correction Packet<BR>(delta fix with targeted feedback)"]

        Scout --> Spec
        Spec --> Packet
        Verify -->|Pass| Commit
        Verify -->|Fail| Correct
    end

    subgraph Inner["Inner Loop (Tactical Execution)"]
        direction TB
        Receive["Read Strategy Packet<BR>(understand exact goal)"]
        Plan["Commit to Execution Plan<BR>(pre-execution diagram)"]
        Execute["Write Code and Run Tests<BR>(no git commits)"]
        Signal["Signal Done<BR>(report result to Outer Loop)"]

        Receive --> Plan
        Plan --> Execute
        Execute --> Signal
    end

    Packet -->|"Handoff (spawn CLI, API call)"| Receive
    Signal -->|"Completion signal"| Verify
    Correct -->|"Delta fix packet"| Receive

    style Outer fill:#e8f4f8,stroke:#2196F3
    style Inner fill:#f0f8e8,stroke:#4CAF50
